    {
        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "We can check version mismatches and missing mods before any modded code is run, so those are reasonably safe to collect together into one big error screen and we should display it as soon as those checks are complete, and completely halt the game before any mods start to load or events are fired.\r\n\r\nI think catching any other errors during other phases while the mods are actually starting up is not safe to do.\r\n\r\nThe error screen is pretty simple, I am not sure what part of the game it needs loaded but it would be worth looking into the bare requirements there so we can display it immediately and stop the game.",
